The `DotGlobeHero` component is a React component designed to display a dynamic, wireframe globe animation as a hero section background. It leverages `react-three-fiber` and `@react-three/drei` to render a 3D globe within a `Canvas` element. The globe features subtle wireframe and mesh layers, with adjustable rotation speed and radius.

## Key Exports

- **`DotGlobeHero`**: The main React component.
- **`DotGlobeHeroProps`**: An interface defining the props for the `DotGlobeHero` component.

## Props

- **`rotationSpeed`**: (Optional) Controls the speed of the globe's rotation. Defaults to `0.005`.
- **`globeRadius`**: (Optional) Determines the radius of the globe. Defaults to `1`.
- **`className`**: (Optional) Custom CSS classes to apply to the main container.
- **`children`**: (Optional) Any React nodes to render on top of the globe, typically for content like headings and text.

## Usage Example

```jsx
import { DotGlobeHero } from '@/components/ui/globe-hero';

function HeroSection() {
  return (
    <DotGlobeHero rotationSpeed={0.01} globeRadius={1.5} className="my-custom-class">
      <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold text-white">Welcome to DocMed</h1>
      <p className="text-lg text-gray-300 mt-4">Explore our documentation</p>
    </DotGlobeHero>
  );
}

export default HeroSection;
```
